WEBVTT

00:02.420 --> 00:03.460
Jude:
I can handle chaos.

00:03.460 --> 00:04.330
Your time in Oakland
would suggest otherwise.

00:04.330 --> 00:05.540
Previously on "The Crossing"...

00:05.540 --> 00:07.580
Here's a quick primer --
all these people here

00:07.580 --> 00:08.710
are from the future.

00:08.710 --> 00:10.290
I think
it's happened before.

00:10.290 --> 00:12.710
There was
an earlier migration.

00:12.710 --> 00:14.580
[ Gunshot ]

00:14.580 --> 00:16.170
[ Gasps ]
[ Body thuds ]

00:16.170 --> 00:18.580
I didn't have a choice.
She knew who I was.

00:18.580 --> 00:21.210
She knew
where we were from.

00:21.210 --> 00:22.540
I'm not
gonna tell anyone.

00:22.540 --> 00:24.960
Then maybe you can be
of use to us.

00:24.960 --> 00:26.880
Why exactly are they keeping you
up at the camp?

00:26.880 --> 00:28.420
It's complicated.

00:28.420 --> 00:30.210
Sophie: Your daughter --
She has Mantle's Disease.

00:30.210 --> 00:31.620
Let me help you
create the treatment,

00:31.620 --> 00:32.920
and then I can take it
back to Leah.

00:32.920 --> 00:34.710
[ Gasps ]

00:34.710 --> 00:37.040
Your mom needs you
to fight.

00:37.040 --> 00:39.120
Jude: Martin. Look, I know
it's been a while,

00:39.120 --> 00:40.620
but I need
some legal advice.

00:40.620 --> 00:42.960
Didn't you learn anything
from the Doucette case?

00:42.960 --> 00:44.120
Put your family
first this time.

00:45.170 --> 00:48.120
[ Siren wails in distance ]

00:48.120 --> 00:51.250
♪♪

00:51.250 --> 00:53.460
Bosco Monroe.

00:53.460 --> 00:55.750
Wanted on two counts
of possession with intent.

00:55.750 --> 00:58.540
We supposed to know this guy?
I've never seen him before.

00:58.540 --> 01:00.250
That's 'cause he just
blew in from L.A.

01:00.250 --> 01:02.710
Got a C.I.
says he's crashing here.

01:02.710 --> 01:04.580
You and Cory take the front.
We'll take the back.

01:04.580 --> 01:06.380
Let's go.

01:08.420 --> 01:10.080
How much you want to bet
Sarge gets a kickback

01:10.080 --> 01:13.000
on this bust
from a rival dealer?

01:13.000 --> 01:14.710
You're kidding, right?

01:14.710 --> 01:17.000
Yeah, yeah,
breaking balls.

01:17.000 --> 01:18.330
Don't do scissors.
Don't do rock.

01:18.330 --> 01:20.920
You always do scissors.
That's so cute.

01:20.920 --> 01:23.330
You're up.

01:23.330 --> 01:25.460
[ Gate creaks ]

01:25.460 --> 01:35.120
♪♪

01:35.120 --> 01:36.460
[ Pounds on door ]

01:36.460 --> 01:38.420
Oakland PD!
Is that a hollow-core door?

01:38.420 --> 01:40.500
This neighborhood's not known
for its quality materials.

01:42.330 --> 01:43.540
Hey, Cory,
I don't know about --

01:43.540 --> 01:44.960
[ Gunshot ]

01:44.960 --> 01:47.210
[ Grunting ]

01:47.210 --> 01:49.540
[ Gunshots ]

01:49.540 --> 01:51.540
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:51.540 --> 01:53.750
[ Indistinct shouting ]
[ Gunshots ]

01:56.750 --> 01:58.920
Central, this is 184 Alpha!

01:58.920 --> 02:00.290
I need a bus!

02:00.290 --> 02:01.710
9-85!

02:01.710 --> 02:03.120
Repeat -- 9-85!

02:03.120 --> 02:04.790
82nd and MacArthur!

02:04.790 --> 02:07.880
I need a bus now!

02:07.880 --> 02:10.420
Hey, Cory, Cory, Cory,
stay with me, bud.

02:10.420 --> 02:13.750
[ Sirens wail in distance ]
Hey, bud, come on.

02:13.750 --> 02:14.960
Hang in there.

02:14.960 --> 02:16.830
Nestor: Jude...
Just stay with me, buddy.

02:16.830 --> 02:19.080
Jude...

02:19.080 --> 02:19.880
Jude?

02:19.880 --> 02:22.120
Yeah.
Yeah, I'm here.

02:22.120 --> 02:25.000
Any idea how long this trip
of yours is gonna take?

02:25.000 --> 02:27.540
[ Sighs ]
Depends on what I find out.

02:27.540 --> 02:29.670
A-And you really think
that this guy can help, huh?

02:29.670 --> 02:31.500
I mean, it's...
not exactly like the Feds

02:31.500 --> 02:33.380
have been
our friends lately.

02:33.380 --> 02:35.750
Look, Emma said that she thought
that there were people

02:35.750 --> 02:38.380
at a high level covering up
this early migration.

02:38.380 --> 02:40.670
If that's true,
then we need high-level access,

02:40.670 --> 02:42.540
and Martin's got it.

02:42.540 --> 02:44.120
And you really trust
this guy, huh?

02:44.120 --> 02:45.330
Yeah.

02:45.330 --> 02:47.290
I mean, he's the only one
I trusted...

02:47.290 --> 02:49.500
the last time.

02:49.500 --> 02:51.210
How'd that work out?

02:53.620 --> 02:57.290
Uh, look,
I-I'll check in later.

02:57.290 --> 02:59.790
[ Cellphone beeps ]

02:59.790 --> 03:02.750
[ Breathes deeply ]

03:02.750 --> 03:04.710
[ Tongue clicks ]

03:14.830 --> 03:17.460
Rebecca: So, you're saying
that Leah is completely healed.

03:17.460 --> 03:19.420
It looks that way.

03:19.420 --> 03:21.080
Her fever's gone,
her vitals are strong,

03:21.080 --> 03:23.880
and she's eating again.

03:23.880 --> 03:25.790
Well, if she's not contagious,
I mean,

03:25.790 --> 03:27.920
she can come back
here with us.
Not just yet.

03:27.920 --> 03:30.000
I've arranged to have her
taken to a hospital in Portland

03:30.000 --> 03:31.580
for a full work-up,
and after she's cleared,

03:31.580 --> 03:33.040
then she can come back.

03:33.040 --> 03:35.580
How did you do it?

03:35.580 --> 03:38.000
Her body's created
a very strong immune response.

03:38.000 --> 03:39.580
It wasn't me, it was her.
She beat it.

03:39.580 --> 03:41.670
No one beats Mantle's.

03:43.920 --> 03:45.830
She's here, isn't she.

03:45.830 --> 03:47.880
Who?

03:47.880 --> 03:50.000
Leah's mother.

03:50.000 --> 03:53.040
You said she
treated her before.
I'm sorry.

03:53.040 --> 03:56.000
I really can't discuss the
particulars of her treatment.

03:56.000 --> 03:59.210
The important thing, Rebecca,
is that she's going to be okay.

04:01.620 --> 04:06.170
Whatever you think you know,
whatever you saw...

04:06.170 --> 04:10.460
you can't trust them.

04:10.460 --> 04:12.540
Apex.

04:12.540 --> 04:20.830
♪♪

04:20.830 --> 04:28.880
♪♪

04:28.880 --> 04:30.420
♪♪

04:30.420 --> 04:32.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:32.420 --> 04:35.620
[ Metal clanking ]

04:35.620 --> 04:37.750
[ Jackhammering ]

04:37.750 --> 04:45.500
♪♪

04:45.500 --> 04:54.000
♪♪

04:54.000 --> 04:59.290
♪♪

04:59.290 --> 05:02.330
I need to talk to Agent Ren
right now.

05:02.330 --> 05:04.080
She's not here.
You can talk to me.

05:04.080 --> 05:06.460
We were led to believe that we'd
be getting out of here soon.

05:06.460 --> 05:09.120
You are.
Then why is there
a fence going up?

05:09.120 --> 05:10.710
Is it to keep people
from coming in or going out?

05:10.710 --> 05:12.380
It's for your protection.

05:12.380 --> 05:14.080
Caleb, there's nothing
to worry about.

05:14.080 --> 05:16.080
A secure perimeter
is standard procedure.

05:18.170 --> 05:21.170
Are we gonna
have a problem?

05:21.170 --> 05:22.750
No.

05:22.750 --> 05:24.460
No problem.

05:26.790 --> 05:29.580
[ Indistinct chatter ]

05:29.580 --> 05:31.290
Cory: How much you want to bet
Sarge gets a kickback

05:31.290 --> 05:33.620
on this bust
from a rival dealer?

05:33.620 --> 05:36.620
Cory found out about Doucette's
little trafficking ring,

05:36.620 --> 05:41.120
so Doucette set up
a fake bust to get rid of Cory.

05:41.120 --> 05:43.500
Shane Doucette
is a decorated veteran.

05:43.500 --> 05:44.880
Mm-hmm.

05:44.880 --> 05:47.040
Commendations
from the Neighborhood Watch

05:47.040 --> 05:49.080
to the State Assembly.

05:49.080 --> 05:51.580
He's also your
commanding officer.
Yeah, good for him.

05:51.580 --> 05:53.830
It doesn't change the fact
that it was a setup.

05:53.830 --> 05:56.170
Look, Doucette wanted
to keep Cory quiet.

05:56.170 --> 05:58.040
He issued a bogus warrant,

05:58.040 --> 06:00.080
hired a disposable junkie
to do the hit,

06:00.080 --> 06:01.920
and then he pumped eight rounds
into him at the scene

06:01.920 --> 06:03.620
to close the loop.

06:03.620 --> 06:05.120
There's strong indications
that Doucette's unit's

06:05.120 --> 06:06.670
running something
out of Eastmont.

06:06.670 --> 06:08.540
Jude found evidence
Cory was compiling against him

06:08.540 --> 06:10.210
before his murder --
forged reports,

06:10.210 --> 06:12.080
transfer receipts,
and surveillance

06:12.080 --> 06:13.210
of more than one shakedown.

06:13.210 --> 06:14.500
Why would they
be that sloppy?

06:14.500 --> 06:17.330
Because they've been getting
away with it for so long.

06:17.330 --> 06:20.420
It's --
It's a good case, sir.

06:20.420 --> 06:23.000
We just need someone like Jude
to step forward.

06:26.620 --> 06:28.500
I'm not in the business
of dissuading officers

06:28.500 --> 06:31.170
from testifying,
but I need you to know,

06:31.170 --> 06:34.670
if we move on this,
word will eventually get out,

06:34.670 --> 06:38.170
and it'll pull most of the force
down on you.

06:38.170 --> 06:41.120
Sergeant Doucette
in particular.

06:41.120 --> 06:42.620
[ Sighs ]

06:42.620 --> 06:45.080
Look...

06:45.080 --> 06:47.290
my partner was murdered,

06:47.290 --> 06:49.620
a murder arranged
by another cop.

06:49.620 --> 06:52.330
If anybody's got a problem with
me seeking justice for Cory,

06:52.330 --> 06:53.960
they can go to hell.

06:56.210 --> 06:58.500
[ Door opens,
door bell jingles ]

07:01.580 --> 07:03.170
You're switching seats
on me, man.
Martin.

07:03.170 --> 07:04.420
No, same table, man.

07:04.420 --> 07:06.790
[ Both laugh ]

07:06.790 --> 07:09.250
Jude, Jude, Jude...

07:11.000 --> 07:12.380
Thank you.

07:12.380 --> 07:14.540
Do you know why
the universe is kind

07:14.540 --> 07:16.380
and there's hope
for us all?

07:16.380 --> 07:17.460
Tell me.

07:17.460 --> 07:19.670
They still have
country-fried steak

07:19.670 --> 07:21.540
with biscuits and gravy
on this menu.

07:21.540 --> 07:23.830
That's why.
[ Laughs ]

07:23.830 --> 07:24.920
You look good, Jude.

07:24.920 --> 07:26.750
Small-town life.
Mm-hmm.

07:26.750 --> 07:30.620
Kicking pain pills
probably didn't hurt, either.

07:30.620 --> 07:32.250
So, over the phone,
you said you're still dealing

07:32.250 --> 07:34.670
with the fallout
from that shipwreck up there?

07:34.670 --> 07:37.170
Yeah.

07:37.170 --> 07:39.670
Yeah, I've been working
with a DHS agent

07:39.670 --> 07:40.830
by the name of Emma Ren.

07:40.830 --> 07:43.540
She's gone missing.

07:43.540 --> 07:46.880
And I think her superior
had something to do with it.

07:46.880 --> 07:49.080
Her superior?
Yeah.

07:49.080 --> 07:51.920
Guy by the name
of Lindauer.

07:51.920 --> 07:53.750
The Deputy Under Secretary?

07:53.750 --> 07:55.460
DHS is holding
a group of people

07:55.460 --> 07:58.460
against their will
in a camp outside my town.

07:58.460 --> 07:59.920
Emma didn't like it.

07:59.920 --> 08:02.540
Lindauer wanted her gone.

08:02.540 --> 08:04.880
First of all, I'm with
the U.S. Attorney's Office now.

08:04.880 --> 08:06.620
Exactly.
You can help me build a case.

08:06.620 --> 08:08.250
I'm telling you this
as a friend --

08:08.250 --> 08:11.120
don't jump
into a volcano again.

08:11.120 --> 08:14.080
Martin, there's
a federal agent missing

08:14.080 --> 08:16.170
and a group of Americans
being detained

08:16.170 --> 08:18.250
against their will
by the U.S. government,

08:18.250 --> 08:20.250
a government that you and I
both represent.

08:23.790 --> 08:27.170
I've got a major trial
about to kick off.

08:27.170 --> 08:30.620
All I can do is send up
a couple of flares,

08:30.620 --> 08:32.710
see if anyone's
heard anything,

08:32.710 --> 08:34.960
see if we can start
putting something together.

08:34.960 --> 08:37.580
I'll take it.

08:37.580 --> 08:39.080
Right now, I'm trying
to determine if you are

08:39.080 --> 08:43.120
the bravest man I know
or the stupidest.

08:43.120 --> 08:44.790
I ask myself that
all the time.

08:44.790 --> 08:46.250
[ Chuckles ]

08:46.250 --> 08:48.080
[ "Ruby Tuesday"
plays on cellphone ]

08:48.080 --> 08:51.830
Marshall:
♪ When the sun is bright ♪

08:51.830 --> 08:54.710
♪ Or in the darkest night ♪

08:54.710 --> 08:58.710
♪ No one knows ♪

08:58.710 --> 09:01.540
♪ She comes and goes ♪

09:01.540 --> 09:04.120
[ Chuckles ]

09:04.120 --> 09:08.250
♪ Goodbye, Ruby Tuesday ♪

09:08.250 --> 09:12.210
♪ Who could hang
a name on you? ♪

09:12.210 --> 09:16.120
♪ When you change
with every new day ♪

09:16.120 --> 09:20.210
♪ Still I'm gonna miss you ♪

09:20.210 --> 09:21.670
[ Chuckles ]

09:21.670 --> 09:22.790
Wow. So that's...

09:22.790 --> 09:23.830
The Stones.

09:23.830 --> 09:25.330
Right.

09:25.330 --> 09:27.380
You're really good.

09:27.380 --> 09:29.080
Do you play
any other instruments?

09:29.080 --> 09:32.330
A little piano.
My mom taught me.

09:32.330 --> 09:35.460
She always wanted
there to be music in the house.

09:35.460 --> 09:37.080
Can you teach me?

09:37.080 --> 09:39.710
Yeah, sure.

09:39.710 --> 09:42.880
If I ever get
to see you again.

09:42.880 --> 09:44.830
So, um,
how do we make that happen?

09:44.830 --> 09:47.710
[ Knock on door, door opens ]

09:47.710 --> 09:50.000
Hey.

09:50.000 --> 09:51.580
I need to talk to him.

09:54.620 --> 09:56.330
Marshall.

09:56.330 --> 09:59.000
Is there anything
in your media about us?

09:59.000 --> 10:01.420
No.

10:01.420 --> 10:03.540
What about people in town?
Do they know?

10:03.540 --> 10:04.880
Most people think
you guys came off

10:04.880 --> 10:06.290
a Russian research vessel

10:06.290 --> 10:07.750
that shipwrecked
off the coast.

10:07.750 --> 10:10.170
Caleb,
did something happen up there?

10:10.170 --> 10:12.380
Yeah, there's a lot more
security.

10:12.380 --> 10:14.000
Fences, guards.

10:15.750 --> 10:18.210
-Let me talk to him!
-Hey, hey, hey!

10:18.210 --> 10:19.540
Caleb. Gabe here.

10:19.540 --> 10:21.040
It's a cover-up.
Gabe?

10:21.040 --> 10:22.620
No, he's good.
He's a friend.

10:22.620 --> 10:23.540
No question.

10:23.540 --> 10:25.830
We can help,
but we need evidence.

10:25.830 --> 10:27.540
What kind of evidence?

10:27.540 --> 10:30.080
Photos. We have to expose
this to the public.

10:30.080 --> 10:31.750
Send us something,
anything.

10:31.750 --> 10:35.830
He's right.
You can use the phone.

10:35.830 --> 10:39.880
Give me about an hour.

10:39.880 --> 10:42.880
I'll be back.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:42.880 --> 10:44.210
South perimeter's
got weak spots.

10:44.210 --> 10:46.210
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

10:46.210 --> 10:49.920
♪♪

10:49.920 --> 10:52.120
Man, people
are gonna freak.

10:52.120 --> 10:59.170
♪♪

10:59.170 --> 11:07.000
♪♪

11:07.000 --> 11:09.960
♪♪

11:09.960 --> 11:12.330
[ Exhales sharply ]
Gut-check time.

11:12.330 --> 11:14.500
We're about to bitch-slap
Homeland Security,

11:14.500 --> 11:15.920
and they ain't
gonna like it.

11:15.920 --> 11:17.960
[ Sighs ]
So?

11:17.960 --> 11:21.790
So, if we do this,
we're in it.

11:21.790 --> 11:24.670
Deep.
Is she worth it?

11:24.670 --> 11:34.040
♪♪

11:34.040 --> 11:36.580
[ Both exhale deeply ]

11:36.580 --> 11:39.920
♪♪

11:43.580 --> 11:52.080
♪♪

11:52.080 --> 12:00.920
♪♪

12:00.920 --> 12:08.000
♪♪

12:08.000 --> 12:10.210
That's impossible.

12:10.210 --> 12:14.000
♪♪

12:14.000 --> 12:15.790
[ Brakes squeal ]

12:17.210 --> 12:19.920
[ Gasps ]

12:19.920 --> 12:21.580
Did anyone follow you?

12:21.580 --> 12:22.960
No.

12:22.960 --> 12:24.540
You said you had photos.

12:24.540 --> 12:26.460
Yes.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

12:30.790 --> 12:33.170
She looks good.

12:33.170 --> 12:35.460
Can you move her?

12:35.460 --> 12:37.620
I'm sending her up to
Portland General this afternoon.

12:37.620 --> 12:39.500
3:00.
Any guards?

12:39.500 --> 12:40.830
Just me.

12:40.830 --> 12:42.540
And if I should happen
to go outside for a walk

12:42.540 --> 12:44.960
and find her gone
when I get back...

12:44.960 --> 12:46.670
I should hope
she was in good hands.

12:49.380 --> 12:51.290
Helping me
puts you in danger.

12:51.290 --> 12:52.790
Why are you doing this?

12:52.790 --> 12:54.670
Maybe I wish my mom
fought as hard for me

12:54.670 --> 12:56.580
as you've fought
for Leah.

13:00.420 --> 13:02.670
Have you ever healed anyone else
with your stem cells?

13:04.620 --> 13:06.750
Just Leah.

13:06.750 --> 13:08.460
Portland General.

13:08.460 --> 13:11.710
Call me when you get there.

13:11.710 --> 13:13.000
[ Engine starts ]

13:13.000 --> 13:20.380
♪♪

13:20.380 --> 13:23.540
♪♪

13:23.540 --> 13:25.460
[ Chuckles ]

13:25.460 --> 13:27.460
[ Laptop chimes ]

13:27.460 --> 13:35.120
♪♪

13:35.120 --> 13:43.120
♪♪

13:43.120 --> 13:44.920
We have reason to believe
that a camera phone

13:44.920 --> 13:46.500
has made its way
onto the premises.

13:46.500 --> 13:48.880
Now, as you all know,
communication devices

13:48.880 --> 13:51.250
are not permitted
inside the camp.

13:51.250 --> 13:53.460
These are Homeland Security
regulations

13:53.460 --> 13:56.540
that my team and I
are required to enforce.

13:56.540 --> 13:59.040
So if anyone knows anything,
if you've seen

13:59.040 --> 14:01.670
an unauthorized person
with a phone

14:01.670 --> 14:03.960
or have the phone
in your possession,

14:03.960 --> 14:06.580
please come to us,
no questions asked.

14:06.580 --> 14:12.790
♪♪

14:12.790 --> 14:15.290
[ Knock on door ]

14:15.290 --> 14:16.960
[ Door creaks ]

14:22.120 --> 14:24.250
Something going on?

14:24.250 --> 14:27.920
We're conducting
a search.

14:27.920 --> 14:29.880
Oh.
So this isn't a social visit.

14:29.880 --> 14:31.750
I'm afraid not.

14:31.750 --> 14:33.960
I have to search
the cabin.

14:41.500 --> 14:43.210
What are you looking for?

14:43.210 --> 14:46.580
Contraband. A phone.

14:46.580 --> 14:49.420
Oh.

14:49.420 --> 14:51.330
What happens
if you're caught with one?

14:51.330 --> 14:53.790
Do you lock us up?

14:53.790 --> 14:56.290
Like we're criminals?

14:56.290 --> 14:58.290
I don't make the rules,
Hannah.

14:58.290 --> 15:00.250
Right.

15:03.960 --> 15:07.830
So what now, pat down?

15:07.830 --> 15:09.330
A strip search?
Should I take my clothes off?

15:09.330 --> 15:10.620
Don't do that.

15:10.620 --> 15:13.460
Don't act like you haven't
been keeping things from me.

15:13.460 --> 15:18.750
♪♪

15:18.750 --> 15:20.880
Sorry.

15:23.040 --> 15:26.290
[ Door opens ]

15:26.290 --> 15:28.120
[ Sighs ]

15:28.120 --> 15:30.250
[ Birds singing ]

15:30.250 --> 15:32.920
[ Metal ringing ]

15:34.500 --> 15:36.670
Hello, Kurt.

15:38.960 --> 15:41.040
What are you doing here?

15:41.040 --> 15:43.170
I need your help.

15:43.170 --> 15:45.290
I tried to help you before,
and you vanished.

15:45.290 --> 15:46.750
Where'd you go?

15:46.750 --> 15:48.330
What have you been doing since
we pulled you out of the water?

15:48.330 --> 15:50.250
It's better
that you don't know.

15:52.710 --> 15:56.540
I need documents,
passports.

15:56.540 --> 15:58.000
And what makes you think
I can help you with that?

15:58.000 --> 16:00.210
[ Speaking Russian ]

16:03.880 --> 16:05.040
That's in the past.

16:10.750 --> 16:12.620
I do know one guy.

16:12.620 --> 16:15.000
But you're gonna need money,
a lot of it.

16:15.000 --> 16:16.830
That won't be a problem.

16:18.960 --> 16:21.040
[ Knock on door ]

16:25.460 --> 16:26.460
Hey, hi.

16:26.460 --> 16:28.500
Hi.

16:28.500 --> 16:30.000
Come on in.

16:30.000 --> 16:32.120
Thank you.

16:36.170 --> 16:38.670
Wait.
You redecorated.

16:38.670 --> 16:42.080
Yeah. Little bit.
Just ready for a new look.

16:42.080 --> 16:44.420
Ah.
Help sell the place, too.

16:44.420 --> 16:46.040
Mm-hmm.

16:46.040 --> 16:47.420
Ollie, your dad's here!

16:47.420 --> 16:50.290
When were you thinking
on doing that, the move?

16:50.290 --> 16:52.120
You know, the plan was
that you and Oliver

16:52.120 --> 16:53.710
would be in Portland
already.

16:53.710 --> 16:55.040
I know, Jude.

16:55.040 --> 16:57.920
Just, uh, wondering.

16:57.920 --> 17:00.120
So, um, what's this case
you're on?

17:00.120 --> 17:01.710
Uh...

17:01.710 --> 17:03.120
Missing persons.

17:03.120 --> 17:07.210
Connected to
a couple other things.

17:07.210 --> 17:10.080
Well, I'd tell you
to be careful.

17:10.080 --> 17:13.880
But I've told you that before
and you didn't listen, so...

17:13.880 --> 17:15.420
I should've.

17:18.380 --> 17:19.380
Hey, baby.
Hey.

17:19.380 --> 17:20.920
Hey.

17:22.000 --> 17:26.210
So, uh...is,
uh...Oliver in bed?

17:26.210 --> 17:28.170
Mm-hmm.
About an hour ago.

17:28.170 --> 17:30.580
An hour ago?
Yep.

17:30.580 --> 17:32.040
Really?

17:35.710 --> 17:37.620
Don't move.

17:37.620 --> 17:41.170
♪♪

17:41.170 --> 17:42.120
Jude...

17:42.120 --> 17:44.080
Hmm?

17:46.830 --> 17:48.790
How did it go today?

17:48.790 --> 17:51.710
It's a go.

17:51.710 --> 17:53.620
The investigation?

17:53.620 --> 17:56.540
Yeah, I go in tomorrow
to give my statement.

17:56.540 --> 17:58.670
Okay.

17:58.670 --> 18:01.830
Do other cops
know that you're testifying?

18:01.830 --> 18:04.250
Like our friends?

18:04.250 --> 18:05.750
Well, I hope not.

18:05.750 --> 18:08.750
There's a chance?

18:08.750 --> 18:10.330
Yeah,
there's always a chance.

18:10.330 --> 18:13.960
Okay.
And then, would we be safe?

18:13.960 --> 18:16.250
Of course.

18:16.250 --> 18:19.420
Look, I love
that you're an optimist,

18:19.420 --> 18:22.210
but can you please just tell me
what we might be looking at?

18:22.210 --> 18:23.920
As a family?

18:23.920 --> 18:28.040
We'll be looking
at doing the right thing.

18:28.040 --> 18:30.040
[ Pills rattle ]

18:30.040 --> 18:33.960
Cory was killed
right in front of me.

18:33.960 --> 18:37.580
Another like 6 inches,

18:37.580 --> 18:40.960
and then it
would've been me.

18:40.960 --> 18:42.580
Doctor said one
every 12 hours.

18:42.580 --> 18:44.420
How many is that today?

18:44.420 --> 18:46.040
Um...

18:46.040 --> 18:48.500
I got shot.

18:48.500 --> 18:50.330
And it hurts.

18:52.080 --> 18:54.880
[ Footsteps ]

18:54.880 --> 18:56.620
Dad!
Oh, dude!

18:56.620 --> 18:58.620
Oh!

18:58.620 --> 19:00.080
How you doing?
Good.

19:00.080 --> 19:01.580
You ready?
Yeah.

19:01.580 --> 19:02.710
Let's do it.
Bye, Mom.

19:02.710 --> 19:04.420
Okay. Have fun.

19:04.420 --> 19:06.040
All right,
here's what I was thinking...

19:06.040 --> 19:15.040
♪♪

19:15.040 --> 19:17.120
[ Speaking Russian ]

19:27.750 --> 19:29.500
Where you from?

19:29.500 --> 19:31.830
Does it matter?

19:31.830 --> 19:34.670
She doesn't look right
to me, Kurt.

19:34.670 --> 19:36.830
I have money.

19:36.830 --> 19:38.170
Where'd you get it?

19:38.170 --> 19:39.420
The bank.

19:39.420 --> 19:41.710
[ Laughter ]

19:41.710 --> 19:43.960
Bank. That's good.

19:43.960 --> 19:48.500
And you wouldn't happen
to be a cop, right?

19:48.500 --> 19:50.710
I don't
have time for this.

19:50.710 --> 19:52.330
What's the --
[ Grunting ]

19:58.670 --> 20:00.330
Open it.

20:00.330 --> 20:07.000
♪♪

20:07.000 --> 20:08.500
Where did you get that?

20:08.500 --> 20:10.920
I told you.

20:10.920 --> 20:13.250
What in the world?

20:13.250 --> 20:15.920
[ Radio chatter ]

20:15.920 --> 20:17.920
That can't be good.

20:21.960 --> 20:24.830
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:29.330 --> 20:31.880
So, did you hear
anything from Marshall?

20:31.880 --> 20:34.250
No.

20:34.250 --> 20:37.250
The way the guards talk,
the Internet seems to be

20:37.250 --> 20:41.000
people's sole preoccupation,
so it should spread fast.

20:43.040 --> 20:45.750
What?

20:45.750 --> 20:49.040
Well, maybe a fence
isn't such a bad thing

20:49.040 --> 20:51.170
if it can protect us
from Apex.

20:51.170 --> 20:54.500
I mean,
what if she comes for her?

20:54.500 --> 20:56.830
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

21:00.120 --> 21:02.120
[ Coughing ]

21:03.540 --> 21:04.960
You okay?

21:04.960 --> 21:06.790
[ Coughing continues ]

21:06.790 --> 21:07.880
Yeah. [ Coughs ]

21:07.880 --> 21:09.790
All right.

21:09.790 --> 21:18.330
♪♪

21:18.330 --> 21:23.580
♪♪

21:23.580 --> 21:25.830
Do you know how many goals
Ronaldo scored

21:25.830 --> 21:27.960
in Champions League?

21:27.960 --> 21:30.330
Uh, 36,000?
No.

21:30.330 --> 21:32.420
Hey, shoes off.

21:32.420 --> 21:33.880
94.

21:33.880 --> 21:36.250
That's 11 goals
ahead of Messi.

21:36.250 --> 21:38.460
Yeah, well,
Messi's played less games.

21:38.460 --> 21:40.960
He'll catch him.
Hey.

21:40.960 --> 21:42.580
Go wash up.

21:48.500 --> 21:53.500
So, uh...Oliver said that you
signed him up for soccer.

21:53.500 --> 21:56.000
That seems like
an odd thing to do to him

21:56.000 --> 21:58.210
if you're gonna
be moving soon.

21:58.210 --> 22:01.540
Unless you're not
moving soon.

22:01.540 --> 22:04.920
♪♪

22:04.920 --> 22:06.830
I met someone.

22:11.580 --> 22:15.120
I'm not trying to keep you
from your son, Jude.

22:15.120 --> 22:18.290
This is the first time
in three years...

22:18.290 --> 22:20.380
that I've been --
I've been happy.

22:20.380 --> 22:22.830
And Oliver's happy.
He has friends here.

22:22.830 --> 22:23.960
He has school.

22:23.960 --> 22:26.830
I moved...

22:26.830 --> 22:30.500
to another state
to take the heat off

22:30.500 --> 22:34.210
so that you and Oliver
would be safe from threats --

22:34.210 --> 22:35.790
And now those threats
are gone,

22:35.790 --> 22:37.420
so why should we
just uproot our lives?

22:37.420 --> 22:41.540
Because that's
what we agreed to!

22:41.540 --> 22:45.170
You want to know
the truth, Jude?

22:45.170 --> 22:49.250
The real threat
wasn't Shane Doucette.

22:49.250 --> 22:51.120
It was you.

23:02.620 --> 23:04.420
Hey, baby.

23:06.710 --> 23:09.290
Hi, baby.

23:09.290 --> 23:11.250
He's supposed to only
call me that at work.

23:11.250 --> 23:12.750
[ Chuckles ]

23:12.750 --> 23:15.210
What's going on, Sergeant?

23:15.210 --> 23:18.750
My wife made
an extra casserole.

23:18.750 --> 23:20.250
Quaint, huh?

23:22.040 --> 23:24.710
Thought I'd do the brotherly
thing and bring you some,

23:24.710 --> 23:28.210
see how your arm's doing.

23:28.210 --> 23:30.080
That's nice.

23:30.080 --> 23:33.330
Like I was telling Amy...

23:33.330 --> 23:35.750
we're all here for you.

23:35.750 --> 23:37.790
The entire unit.

23:37.790 --> 23:41.830
You need anything,
just ask.

23:41.830 --> 23:45.000
'Cause family looks out
for one another, right?

23:47.750 --> 23:50.750
We are family...

23:50.750 --> 23:52.380
aren't we, Jude?

23:52.380 --> 23:55.830
Yeah. Of course.

23:55.830 --> 23:58.580
Enjoy the casserole.

23:58.580 --> 24:07.500
♪♪

24:07.500 --> 24:08.580
Jude...

24:08.580 --> 24:10.290
It's okay.

24:10.290 --> 24:12.380
No, it's not.

24:12.380 --> 24:14.580
I'll call my guy
at Internal Affairs

24:14.580 --> 24:15.750
and tell him
what just happened.

24:15.750 --> 24:18.330
[ Sighs ]

24:18.330 --> 24:20.080
I knew Cory.

24:20.080 --> 24:23.080
He was my friend, too.

24:23.080 --> 24:24.920
He wouldn't
want this for us, Jude.

24:24.920 --> 24:26.330
What are you talking about?

24:26.330 --> 24:28.170
He wouldn't want
you and me

24:28.170 --> 24:29.880
and our son
to feel unsafe.

24:29.880 --> 24:33.290
Are you telling me
I should drop the case?

24:33.290 --> 24:36.710
This isn't
just about Cory.

24:36.710 --> 24:40.500
This is about
every honest cop out there.

24:40.500 --> 24:42.170
Huh? Well, okay.
What do you want me to do?

24:42.170 --> 24:45.040
Stick my head
in the sand?

24:45.040 --> 24:47.790
And -- And let Doucette
and the rest of his crew

24:47.790 --> 24:50.460
keep chopping down
this city?

24:50.460 --> 24:52.710
Okay, what happens
to the next guy

24:52.710 --> 24:55.040
who goes up against them
like Cory did?

24:55.040 --> 24:58.330
You're that next guy.

24:58.330 --> 25:00.960
Don't you understand?

25:00.960 --> 25:03.620
I'm not gonna
hide from this.

25:03.620 --> 25:05.790
Then I'm taking Oliver.
We're gonna go stay with my mom.

25:05.790 --> 25:09.380
Oh, please, Amy, geez.

25:12.120 --> 25:14.380
It's your family
or this case.

25:18.880 --> 25:22.210
Say hi to your mom.

25:22.210 --> 25:24.500
[ Cellphone ringing ]

25:29.920 --> 25:32.420
[ Cellphone beeps ]

25:32.420 --> 25:34.710
Yeah.
Martin: Good news.

25:34.710 --> 25:36.880
I got a guy from Justice
who wants to talk.

25:36.880 --> 25:38.170
Says he might
have something for you.

25:38.170 --> 25:41.460
You got a pen?

25:41.460 --> 25:43.380
Yeah.

25:48.960 --> 25:51.080
[ Birds singing ]

25:52.750 --> 25:54.750
Dr. Forbin,
thank you for coming.

25:54.750 --> 25:56.210
I hope it wasn't
an inconvenience.

25:56.210 --> 25:58.920
No, not at all.

25:58.920 --> 26:00.920
They call this
a cortado.

26:00.920 --> 26:02.880
It's Spanish. Wonderful.
You want one?

26:02.880 --> 26:06.580
No, thank you. Caffeine and I
don't really mix.

26:06.580 --> 26:08.330
You've done amazing work.

26:08.330 --> 26:10.250
Clearing the camp
of that contagion.

26:10.250 --> 26:12.420
That little girl
owes you her life.

26:12.420 --> 26:15.000
Well, she's stronger
than she looks.

26:15.000 --> 26:16.880
I'm not a scientist,
so there's, uh --

26:16.880 --> 26:18.210
it's probably
not worth me asking,

26:18.210 --> 26:20.040
but how did you
treat her?

26:20.040 --> 26:22.170
Well, thanks to Agent Ren
and your staff,

26:22.170 --> 26:23.750
Leah was isolated
immediately.

26:23.750 --> 26:25.620
I then used
a combination of potent,

26:25.620 --> 26:28.080
broad-spectrum antivirals.

26:28.080 --> 26:31.080
That seemed
to do the trick.

26:31.080 --> 26:33.670
Well, I'd like to thank you
for your service.

26:33.670 --> 26:35.960
And if there's ever anything
the Department can do

26:35.960 --> 26:38.290
to return the favor,
do let me know.

26:40.880 --> 26:42.670
Sir, there's more
to be done --

26:42.670 --> 26:44.580
Leah's follow-up,
research that could be benef--

26:44.580 --> 26:48.420
That is one area where I'm sorry
to say I can't be of help.

26:48.420 --> 26:50.460
Your research all belongs
to the government now,

26:50.460 --> 26:52.920
and your services
are no longer required.

26:52.920 --> 26:55.670
I'm sure you understand.

26:55.670 --> 27:04.080
♪♪

27:04.080 --> 27:10.290
♪♪

27:10.290 --> 27:12.710
[ Radio chatter ]

27:15.460 --> 27:18.120
Name?
Sophie Forbin.
I work here.

27:18.120 --> 27:21.380
My lab is here.
I have to get to my research.

27:21.380 --> 27:23.540
I'm sorry, ma'am. You're listed
here as restricted.

27:23.540 --> 27:25.290
No access.
Well, I was just
here this morning.

27:25.290 --> 27:26.790
If I could just get inside,
five minutes --

27:26.790 --> 27:29.000
I can't allow it, ma'am.
Damn it, just listen to m--

27:29.000 --> 27:30.290
[ Groans ]

27:30.290 --> 27:32.580
Are you okay?

27:32.580 --> 27:40.210
♪♪

27:40.210 --> 27:45.500
♪♪

27:45.500 --> 27:47.580
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

27:47.580 --> 27:49.420
Yeah?
Caleb, i-it's me.

27:49.420 --> 27:52.210
Is everything all right
on your end?

27:52.210 --> 27:55.080
No. They're doing
spot checks for phones.

27:55.080 --> 27:57.210
Pictures must have got
the attention of DHS,

27:57.210 --> 27:58.580
'cause they're spinning
the entire story,

27:58.580 --> 28:00.620
changing it,
calling it a hoax.

28:00.620 --> 28:02.670
What does that mean?
What are they saying?

28:02.670 --> 28:04.960
Caleb.

28:04.960 --> 28:07.500
Give me the phone.

28:11.830 --> 28:12.580
Marshall: Hello?

28:12.580 --> 28:14.250
Caleb?

28:14.250 --> 28:16.250
Hello?

28:23.540 --> 28:26.380
Where'd you get it?
From a guard?

28:26.380 --> 28:30.080
I'll answer your questions
after you answer mine.

28:30.080 --> 28:32.670
Why are we being fenced in
and hidden away?

28:32.670 --> 28:35.040
You're being protected,
not hidden.

28:35.040 --> 28:36.170
Then why can't I
have a phone?

28:36.170 --> 28:38.290
Why can't we
talk to people?

28:38.290 --> 28:40.500
Those are our rules.

28:40.500 --> 28:42.620
[ Crowd murmuring ]

28:42.620 --> 28:45.330
Take the phone.

28:45.330 --> 28:47.540
Roy, the phone, now!

28:47.540 --> 28:51.420
♪♪

28:51.420 --> 28:53.500
Let the man talk.

28:53.500 --> 28:56.420
Listen, we've done everything
you've asked of us.

28:56.420 --> 28:58.500
And Agent Ren,
she assured us

28:58.500 --> 29:00.500
that we were on a path
to citizenship.

29:00.500 --> 29:02.960
Now she's gone,
and walls are going up.

29:02.960 --> 29:04.710
It's not what you think.

29:04.710 --> 29:07.460
Look, this is
not a prison.

29:07.460 --> 29:09.620
You make promises,

29:09.620 --> 29:11.420
but you don't have
the power to keep them.

29:11.420 --> 29:14.460
You're just another one
of their lapdogs.

29:14.460 --> 29:16.420
You want to be a good dog?

29:16.420 --> 29:17.880
Here.

29:24.620 --> 29:27.170
Go fetch.

29:27.170 --> 29:33.420
♪♪

29:33.420 --> 29:35.920
Fall back.

29:35.920 --> 29:38.580
Everything's fine, folks.

29:38.580 --> 29:40.420
-It's okay, it's okay.
-Just go about your day.

29:40.420 --> 29:42.710
You can go back
to your cabins.

29:42.710 --> 29:44.170
It's fine.

29:52.380 --> 30:01.500
♪♪

30:01.500 --> 30:06.920
♪♪

30:06.920 --> 30:09.580
[ Fence creaks ]

30:09.580 --> 30:12.170
♪♪

30:12.170 --> 30:15.080
[ Elevator bell dings ]
Jude:
Is that a hollow-core?

30:15.080 --> 30:19.580
♪♪

30:19.580 --> 30:25.960
♪♪

30:25.960 --> 30:28.120
[ Elevator bell dings ]

30:28.120 --> 30:30.750
I don't know about this.

30:30.750 --> 30:38.750
♪♪

30:38.750 --> 30:40.920
[ Elevator door closes ]

30:40.920 --> 30:45.210
♪♪

30:45.210 --> 30:48.540
[ Birds singing ]

30:48.540 --> 30:50.500
[ Toy squeaks ]
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

30:53.290 --> 30:54.540
Is she there?
Sophie: No.

30:54.540 --> 30:56.210
Something happened.
They cut me off.

30:56.210 --> 30:57.460
I couldn't get
into the camp,

30:57.460 --> 31:00.330
I couldn't get to Leah.

31:00.330 --> 31:01.790
Reece --

31:01.790 --> 31:04.000
It's okay.

31:04.000 --> 31:06.330
I should've known
it'd go like this.

31:06.330 --> 31:07.790
Reece, where are you?
I'll come to you.

31:07.790 --> 31:09.040
I need to see you.

31:09.040 --> 31:10.880
I got to go.
Reece, please.

31:10.880 --> 31:13.170
What your cells did for Leah,
it was miraculous.

31:13.170 --> 31:15.000
I know -- I know I don't have
a right to ask,

31:15.000 --> 31:16.670
but if I could just get
another sample...

31:16.670 --> 31:19.750
I told you -- no blood,
no organic materials.

31:19.750 --> 31:21.500
You're a cure, Reece.

31:21.500 --> 31:24.710
You're the answer to every
illness, every human defect.

31:24.710 --> 31:27.420
I mean, do you have any idea
how many lives you could save?

31:27.420 --> 31:30.540
Not 50 years from now,
not 200, today.

31:30.540 --> 31:32.790
I'm not here to save
anyone else's life.

31:32.790 --> 31:34.170
I just want Leah.

31:34.170 --> 31:36.000
You could save my life.

31:37.790 --> 31:40.580
I'm sorry.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

31:40.580 --> 31:42.750
[ Grunts ]

31:42.750 --> 31:49.750
♪♪

31:49.750 --> 31:51.920
[ Grunting ]

31:54.620 --> 31:57.250
[ Gasping ]

31:57.250 --> 32:03.500
♪♪

32:03.500 --> 32:07.750
[ Horn honking ]

32:07.750 --> 32:09.880
[ Metal crunches ]

32:09.880 --> 32:12.710
[ Honking continues ]

32:18.960 --> 32:20.830
[ Elevator bell dings ]

32:25.540 --> 32:27.960
Just don't say it.

32:27.960 --> 32:30.380
I'm sorry, Jude.
No indictment.

32:30.380 --> 32:32.540
Someone is protecting him.

32:35.170 --> 32:36.670
Maybe next time,
huh, brother?

32:36.670 --> 32:38.080
Yeah, maybe.
All right, you be good.

32:38.080 --> 32:39.170
Yeah, hey.

32:39.170 --> 32:40.710
-Unh!
-Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

32:40.710 --> 32:42.620
Stop it! Hey, man!

32:42.620 --> 32:43.790
Next time!

32:43.790 --> 32:45.710
It's not worth it!
Stop.

32:45.710 --> 32:48.290
Okay. Sorry.

32:48.290 --> 32:49.380
Okay. Sorry.

32:49.380 --> 32:50.710
We can appeal.
Let's appeal, okay?

32:50.710 --> 32:53.790
No, we can't, we can't.
He made a deal.

32:53.790 --> 32:55.670
We lost, Jude.

32:55.670 --> 32:57.000
It's over.

32:57.000 --> 32:59.580
[ Breathing heavily ]

33:06.420 --> 33:08.670
[ Door bell jingles ]

33:15.000 --> 33:17.710
You blew off the meeting.

33:17.710 --> 33:19.500
Something...

33:19.500 --> 33:21.960
just didn't feel right.

33:21.960 --> 33:25.540
All I did was run information
up the chain.

33:25.540 --> 33:29.380
In the meantime, I did
some checking into Lindauer.

33:29.380 --> 33:31.210
He's some sort of prodigy.

33:31.210 --> 33:33.290
Scary smart.

33:33.290 --> 33:35.580
He only joined DHS
nine years ago,

33:35.580 --> 33:39.710
and that is
an awfully fast track.

33:39.710 --> 33:41.580
Former systems geek.

33:41.580 --> 33:45.170
Threat assessment,
emergency preparedness.

33:45.170 --> 33:48.120
Apparently, he has a real knack
for "predictive modeling."

33:48.120 --> 33:50.420
They say that he could
spotlight issues

33:50.420 --> 33:52.000
almost before anyone else
knew they were issues,

33:52.000 --> 33:52.790
almost like he could --

33:52.790 --> 33:54.920
Tell the future.

33:54.920 --> 33:56.670
Exactly.

33:59.120 --> 34:01.170
And this...

34:01.170 --> 34:03.960
is where we say goodbye,
Jude.

34:03.960 --> 34:06.040
Take care of yourself,
though.

34:09.080 --> 34:10.210
I hope I never
see you again.

34:10.210 --> 34:12.670
[ Both laugh ]

34:12.670 --> 34:14.210
Thank you.

34:16.920 --> 34:17.880
[ Door opens,
door bell jingles ]

34:17.880 --> 34:20.000
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

34:23.920 --> 34:25.330
Hello?

34:25.330 --> 34:28.580
Sheriff Ellis?
Craig Lindauer.

34:28.580 --> 34:31.790
I understand you've been asking
questions about me.

34:31.790 --> 34:33.250
A few.

34:33.250 --> 34:37.330
I wish you would've
just come to me first.

34:37.330 --> 34:39.880
Well, let's just say
that your department

34:39.880 --> 34:43.750
has been less
than inviting.

34:43.750 --> 34:45.670
Why don't you give me
a chance to remedy that?

34:45.670 --> 34:47.750
I can come to you.

34:47.750 --> 34:52.250
♪♪

34:52.250 --> 34:55.790
Batton Inlet Bridge,
10:00.

34:55.790 --> 34:58.000
Okay.

34:58.000 --> 34:59.830
I'll see you there.

34:59.830 --> 35:05.790
♪♪

35:05.790 --> 35:08.830
[ Monitors beeping ]

35:08.830 --> 35:11.000
[ Inhales sharply ]

35:11.000 --> 35:17.540
♪♪

35:17.540 --> 35:23.880
♪♪

35:23.880 --> 35:25.920
[ Door opens, closes ]

35:25.920 --> 35:29.170
Sophie.

35:29.170 --> 35:32.750
I'm afraid
I don't have good news.

35:32.750 --> 35:35.000
I know.

35:35.000 --> 35:36.580
I can see.

35:36.580 --> 35:44.170
♪♪

35:44.170 --> 35:45.790
[ Drawer opens ]

35:47.710 --> 35:48.790
[ Drawer closes ]

35:48.790 --> 35:50.880
[ Gasps ]

35:54.170 --> 35:56.040
What is it?

35:56.040 --> 35:58.460
Something wrong
with the documents?

35:58.460 --> 36:00.620
I need something else.

36:00.620 --> 36:09.540
♪♪

36:09.540 --> 36:11.710
♪♪

36:11.710 --> 36:13.250
[ Bag zips ]

36:13.250 --> 36:15.710
♪♪

36:19.830 --> 36:21.420
[ Insects chirping ]

36:26.290 --> 36:34.830
♪♪

36:34.830 --> 36:40.580
♪♪

36:40.580 --> 36:42.250
[ Cork pops ]

36:44.420 --> 36:46.750
[ Knock on door ]

36:46.750 --> 36:49.460
[ Sighs ]

36:49.460 --> 36:56.830
♪♪

36:56.830 --> 37:00.250
♪♪

37:00.250 --> 37:02.920
Hey.
You got a sec?

37:02.920 --> 37:05.120
Yeah, sure.
Come -- Come on in.

37:10.170 --> 37:12.500
I admire the way
you handled yourself today.

37:12.500 --> 37:14.960
We all did.

37:14.960 --> 37:15.960
Except none of that
would've happened

37:15.960 --> 37:18.380
if you didn't
sell me out.

37:18.380 --> 37:21.380
Me? [ Scoffs ]

37:21.380 --> 37:22.790
Y-You think
I said something?

37:22.790 --> 37:24.830
Oh, I know you did.

37:24.830 --> 37:28.120
As sure as I know
that's alcohol on your breath.

37:28.120 --> 37:30.290
What I don't know
is why.

37:34.080 --> 37:37.080
So what? You, um --
You came here to torture me?

37:37.080 --> 37:38.620
Is that it?

37:38.620 --> 37:41.040
You know, back home,
each man in our unit,

37:41.040 --> 37:44.080
they developed their own
method for flushing out rats.

37:44.080 --> 37:45.830
Me?

37:45.830 --> 37:49.880
I always looked
for two things.

37:49.880 --> 37:54.540
And when I confirm those things,
then I torture.

37:54.540 --> 37:56.710
Come on, man.
[ Chuckles ]

37:56.710 --> 37:58.710
This is crazy.

37:58.710 --> 38:02.170
You come here in the middle
of the night to accuse me?

38:02.170 --> 38:03.170
Who the hell
do you think you are?

38:03.170 --> 38:05.120
It wasn't me.

38:05.120 --> 38:08.750
One. Snitches tend to get
defensive when they are accused.

38:08.750 --> 38:11.710
Because I didn't do it!

38:11.710 --> 38:13.120
You want a rat,
why -- why --

38:13.120 --> 38:15.460
why don't you go ask
that guy Paul?

38:15.460 --> 38:17.040
I've seen him hanging
around the camp.

38:17.040 --> 38:18.000
He's schmoozing
all the agents.

38:18.000 --> 38:21.330
Yeah, two --
they deflect blame.

38:21.330 --> 38:25.170
Point at others
to save themselves.

38:25.170 --> 38:27.040
Okay, I did it! I did it!
I did it!

38:27.040 --> 38:29.670
I've been giving information
to a guard.

38:29.670 --> 38:33.750
He told me the phone
was a serious thing.

38:33.750 --> 38:35.040
I didn't -- Well, I didn't want
that to jeopardize

38:35.040 --> 38:37.830
my chances
of getting out again.

38:37.830 --> 38:39.540
Don't -- Don't hurt me.

38:41.830 --> 38:43.420
You know what?

38:45.380 --> 38:49.040
All right.
Tell you what I'm gonna do.

38:49.040 --> 38:51.250
I'm gonna make you a deal.

38:51.250 --> 38:53.580
But you got
to keep this quiet, okay?

38:53.580 --> 38:55.250
Because you're right.

38:55.250 --> 38:57.000
We don't want to jeopardize
our chances here, right?

38:57.000 --> 38:59.380
Yes! Exactly.
Thank you.

38:59.380 --> 39:01.960
So, here's the deal --

39:01.960 --> 39:04.460
I agree not to kill you...

39:04.460 --> 39:07.420
and you agree not to tell anyone
who did this.

39:07.420 --> 39:09.380
Did what?

39:09.380 --> 39:10.500
[ Bone cracks ]
Aah! Aah!

39:10.500 --> 39:11.880
Shh!

39:11.880 --> 39:15.540
[ Muffled screaming ]

39:15.540 --> 39:17.880
[ Groans ]

39:17.880 --> 39:21.210
♪♪

39:23.880 --> 39:26.250
[ Siren chirps ]

39:31.710 --> 39:34.120
[ Radio chatter ]

39:39.170 --> 39:40.500
License and registration.

39:40.500 --> 39:43.120
I'm a government agent
with Homeland Security.

39:43.120 --> 39:45.210
License and registration,
sir.

39:45.210 --> 39:47.210
I don't have it with me.

39:47.210 --> 39:48.830
I'm happy to show you
my credentials.

39:48.830 --> 39:51.540
Keep your hands where I can
see them, please.

39:51.540 --> 39:55.080
So, your driving was, uh,
a little erratic back there.

39:55.080 --> 39:56.380
You weren't texting,
were you?

39:56.380 --> 39:59.830
No, I wasn't texting.

39:59.830 --> 40:01.210
[ Knock on window ]

40:04.540 --> 40:06.290
[ Whistles ]
[ Window motor whirring ]

40:10.000 --> 40:11.960
This is a nice car.

40:11.960 --> 40:12.830
And you know what?

40:12.830 --> 40:14.830
I-I'll bet in like...

40:14.830 --> 40:17.830
180 years,
they're still driving Caddies.

40:17.830 --> 40:20.040
Sheriff Ellis, I presume.

40:20.040 --> 40:22.880
Nice putting
a face to the name, huh?

40:22.880 --> 40:24.460
Lindauer.

40:26.960 --> 40:29.080
You smell that, Deputy?

40:29.080 --> 40:31.080
I do. Alcohol.

40:31.080 --> 40:34.120
Yeah.
How 'bout that?

40:34.120 --> 40:36.000
Ask you to step out
of the vehicle, sir.

40:36.000 --> 40:37.250
[ Car door dinging ]

40:37.250 --> 40:38.540
We need to search
your vehicle.

40:38.540 --> 40:41.540
Okay.

40:41.540 --> 40:43.750
How's about we keep those hands
where I can see them, okay?

40:43.750 --> 40:45.790
Right up here.

40:45.790 --> 40:48.210
[ Car door closes ]

40:48.210 --> 40:49.960
Oh.

40:51.580 --> 40:53.000
Look what I found.

40:53.000 --> 40:56.290
With the, uh,
serial number shaved off.

40:56.290 --> 40:58.540
I procured it in the course
of an investigation.

40:58.540 --> 41:00.710
I just haven't had a chance
to voucher it yet.

41:00.710 --> 41:03.040
I don't buy it.
Me neither.

41:03.040 --> 41:05.710
Hands behind
your back, sir.

41:05.710 --> 41:07.880
Hands behind
your back now.

41:07.880 --> 41:10.620
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

41:10.620 --> 41:12.790
This really the play
you want to make, Sheriff?

41:12.790 --> 41:14.710
Get your ass in the car.

41:14.710 --> 41:16.580
Let's go.

41:16.580 --> 41:22.750
♪♪

41:22.750 --> 41:29.750
♪♪
